title: Another note from mom
author: aaron
text: i sprang from bed and bumped my head and stubbed my little toe,  then jammed my fingers turning down the blaring radio.   i rubbed my bumps and bruises as the weather lady said,   ''today's the first of april,  look for showers overhead. ''  i trudged downstairs to breakfast,  where my bad luck tagged along.  there taped up to the microwave…another note from mom:  good morning! exclamation point-she always starts out nice.  now comes the part where i get fed her motherly advice.   for breakfast,  dear,  just help yourself.  there's pizza in the fridge.   and as for soda,  choose the sprite-the coke has lost its fizz.   ''is this a dream?'' i said out loud.  ''there must be some mistake.  i'd better read that through again.  i'm only half awake. ''  i scanned the lines,  not once,  but twice.  yes,  pizza's what it said! and i could swallow that advice,  so i read on ahead:  please wear your faded jeans to school,  those low-cut ones that flare.  and use my mousse to do that sticky-up thing with your hair.   ''is she for real?'' i asked myself.  what's gotten into mom? whatever it was,  i liked it lots,  so i continued on:  about your science quiz today-the one on natural gas- just tell your teacher that's one subject you don't want to pass!  i know i didn't read that right.  i couldn't have,  no way! but there it was in black and white,  as plain as night and day.   and then it hit me,  why the change: mom hadn't lost a screw; my worry-free philosophy had finally gotten through.   her rules had changed from lame to lax-my mom was cool at last! these last few months of middle school were gonna be a blast!  i quickly read the last few lines: enjoy your day at school!  (and don't believe what you've just read…or you're an april fool!)

text: soothness is lavender like an open window with the wind breezing by.  it is flowing like a cup of creamed cofee streaming down my throat.  it makes me calm like branches swaying on a carribean coast.

title: Fear
author: alexandra
text: fear is dark like eyes staring straight at you.  it seeps through my mind like a machine crushing ice.  it scares me like a deer running from cars.

title: the bee
author: alexandra
text: the bee came with me the bee had a pee  the bee was glee

title: Piggies
author: alexandra
text: pink is a piggies little springy tail.  cool is a roll in the soothing brown mud.  it sounds like a snoring man.  smooth like sand on an ocean's coast.  moves like a lazy bum.

title: Ogs
author: alexandra
text: the dogs log sits in the bush hiding from the soggy doggy.

title: Love
author: alexandra
text: a trick of love  kept in heat of slow movment,  of great love writing in your diary.

title: Stress
author: alexandra
text: how did i do? i don't know! did i fail? i hope not.  this is much stress! what to do,  what to do? do i sit back and wait or do i go ask the teacher now? so many choices,  so many choices! i think i will sit back and wait.  i know i did not do well in social studies,  i stink at that kind of stuff! oh now he is passing them out! oh my, i passed! thank god i passed and i did the best in social studies! weird huh.  shows what stress can do to you!

title: My Puppy
author: alexandra
text: my puppy is the best,  he's very clean,  very keen,  and cuter than the rest!

title: Winter is Near
author: alexandra
text: the wind is stronger the air is cold as i walk i see leaves  falling and changing i see reds,  browns,  yellows,   and many others i'm going to school but there is one difference i'm wearing a hat,  scarf,  and mittens my nose is red and so are my ears and when i hear the icy cold wind whisper my name  i know that  winter is near!!

title: Spring
author: alexandra
text: hooray spring is here  no more of the cold white snow  hooray spring is here

title: Suger Plums
author: alexandra
text: in the night  the suger plums open up a world  of  magic,  the suger plum fairys  dance to the rhytem of a flute.  they dance till dawn. when the sun rises they turn back into suger plums.

title: Kindness and Friendship
author: alexandra
text: kindness fits hand in hand with friendship,  helps you get along.   sometimes. . . friends forget that they are supposed to have a soul of kindness . . . sometimes.   friends help you get along in life,  and definitely. . .  help you to find your own way.   friends can have bumpy phases but that will change.  you will help them. . .  hopefully.   kindness fits hand in hand with friendship,  helps you get along.

title: Pickle
author: alexandra
text: my mommy bought me a pickle.  it is green and bumpy.  i think i'll name it grumpy.  i love my little grumpy,  because he is so bumpy.

title: My Ball
author: alexandra
text: my ball is big and round.  my ball can bounce 10 feet  high.  my ball is  better than yours.  it can do all sorts of tricks.  i  love  my ball.

title: I love books
author: alexandria
text: books are great.   they dont taste to great.   read one and youll see how great.
